tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE feature_engineering (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    feature_name VARCHAR(255),
    data_type VARCHAR(50),
    transformation VARCHAR(50),
    importance DECIMAL
);

CREATE TABLE model_training (
    model_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    model_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    training_accuracy DECIMAL(5,2),
    validation_accuracy DECIMAL(5,2)
);

CREATE TABLE PredictionResults (
    prediction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    input_data TEXT,
    predicted_output TEXT,
    confidence_level FLOAT,
    prediction_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE feature_model_relationship (
  relationship_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  feature_id INT,
  model_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (feature_id) REFERENCES feature_engineering(feature_id),
  FOREIGN KEY (model_id) REFERENCES predictive_modeling(model_id)
);

CREATE TABLE feature_engineering (
    feature_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    feature_name VARCHAR(255),
    feature_type VARCHAR(50),
    is_categorical BOOL,
    is_numerical BOOL
);

CREATE TABLE model_training (
    model_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(255),
    model_type VARCHAR(50),
    training_dataset_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (training_dataset_id) REFERENCES feature_engineering(feature_id)
);

CREATE TABLE evaluation_metrics (
    evaluation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    metric_name VARCHAR(255),
    metric_value DOUBLE,
    model_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (model_id) REFERENCES model_training(model_id)
);

CREATE TABLE prediction_results (
    prediction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    prediction_value DOUBLE,
    model_id INT,
    evaluation_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (model_id) REFERENCES model_training(model_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (evaluation_id) REFERENCES evaluation_metrics(evaluation_id)
);
